Document: GradientTexture1D
Path: godot/classes/class_gradienttexture1d.rst
Summary: A 1D texture that generates colors by sampling a Gradient for each pixel, with potential color approximation due to pixel limitations.

A 1D texture that obtains colors from a Gradient to fill the texture data. The texture is filled by sampling the gradient for each pixel. Therefore, the texture does not necessarily represent an exact copy of the gradient, as it may miss some colors if there are not enough pixels. See also GradientTexture2D, CurveTexture and CurveXYZTexture.
---CHUNK---
Document: GradientTexture1D
Path: godot/classes/class_gradienttexture1d.rst
Summary: Properties of GradientTexture1D including gradient, resource_local_to_scene, use_hdr, and width with their types, descriptions, and default values.

gradient (Gradient): The gradient to use. Overrides Resource's resource_local_to_scene. Default: false.
resource_local_to_scene (bool): Whether the resource is local to the scene. Note: Overrides Resource's resource_local_to_scene. Default: false.
use_hdr (bool): Whether to use HDR format. Default: false.
width (int): The width of the texture. Default: 256.
